reply_content:
@jheaaa-u7s I'm sorry if my wording caused any misunderstanding.
I’m not claiming that death game or battle royale-style stories originated in Japan.
I just wanted to counter the argument that Japanese works were influenced by Squid Game, even though Japan had already produced many similar death game stories long before Squid Game existed.

@DavJK36 You're right . I should have just enjoyed the work purely, like you do.
I regret getting too negative about it...
I'm looking forward to this one too!

@maktiki
This movie is set in Japan during the Meiji era.
At that time, the Japanese government encouraged its citizens to adopt Western hairstyles instead of the traditional topknot (mage) in order to catch up with the advanced countries overseas.
